content:
Invoke an Omni-Channel Flow to Route Non-Real-Time Objects

To route non-real-time objects, such as cases, leads, and custom objects, define the routing logic in an Omni-Channel flow. Invoke the flow from a parent flow based on your business rules.

Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer Editions with the Service Cloud

To invoke an Omni-Channel flow for a non-real-time object, follow these steps:

1. In the Quick Find box under Setup, enter Flows.
2. Click New Flow.
3. Click Record-Triggered Flow, and then click Create.
4. Select the non-real-time object, such as Case.
5. Trigger the subflow when a record is created.
6. Add a Subflow element to the flow by dragging it from the Elements toolbox.
7. Select the Omni-Channel flow in the New Subflow window.
8. Enter the label and API name for the subflow element.
9. Connect the elements in the flow by dragging the Start element onto the Subflow element.

Save the record-triggered flow.
title: Service Cloud Omni-Channel Flows
